  "steps": [
    {
      "order": 1,
      "instruction": "Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F. Grease a square baking dish or 10 inch skillet."
    },
    {
      "order": 2,
      "instruction": "Line the croissants, cut side up, in the baking dish and place a small pat of butter on each. Add the turkey in an even layer and then drizzle the gravy overtop. Top with a layer of cheese and then add the prosciutto. Arrange the tater tots in an even layer. Transfer to the oven and bake for 30-40 minutes or until the tater tots are crisp. Serve!"
